concept_explanation.bucket4j:
**Bucket4j token bucket rate limiter:**

```java
// pom.xml: com.bucket4j:bucket4j-core + bucket4j-redis

@Component
public class RateLimitingFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    private final LoadingCache<String, Bucket> buckets = Caffeine.newBuilder()
        .expireAfterAccess(1, TimeUnit.HOURS)
        .build(this::newBucket);

    private Bucket newBucket(String merchantId) {
        return Bucket.builder()
            .addLimit(Bandwidth.classic(100, Refill.greedy(100, Duration.ofMinutes(1))))
            // 100 tokens, refills 100/min (greedy = immediately starts refilling)
            .build();
    }

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res,
                                    FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {
        String merchantId = extractMerchantId(req);  // from JWT claim or API key
        if (merchantId == null) { chain.doFilter(req, res); return; }

        Bucket bucket = buckets.get(merchantId);
        if (bucket.tryConsume(1)) {
            // Token available: let request through
            res.setHeader('X-RateLimit-Remaining', String.valueOf(bucket.getAvailableTokens()));
            chain.doFilter(req, res);
        } else {
            // Bucket empty: rate limited!
            res.setStatus(429);  // Too Many Requests
            res.setHeader('Retry-After', '60');
            res.setHeader('X-RateLimit-Limit', '100');
            res.setHeader('X-RateLimit-Reset', String.valueOf(
                System.currentTimeMillis() / 1000 + 60));
            res.getWriter().write('{"error":"rate_limit_exceeded","retryAfter":60}');
        }
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.distributed:
**Distributed rate limiting with Redis:**
```java
// For multiple pod instances: each pod has its own in-memory Caffeine bucket
// Problem: 10 pods, each allows 100 req/min → merchant can send 1000 req/min!
// Fix: share rate limit state in Redis (atomic operations)

// Bucket4j + Redis (Bucket4j Pro or OSS with Redisson):
Redisson redisson = RedissonClient.create(...);
BucketConfiguration config = BucketConfiguration.builder()
    .addLimit(Bandwidth.classic(100, Refill.greedy(100, Duration.ofMinutes(1))))
    .build();
ProxyManager<String> proxyManager = Bucket4jRedisson.entryPointOf(redisson);

// Each merchantId gets a Redis-backed bucket:
Bucket bucket = proxyManager.builder().build('rate:' + merchantId, ()-> config);
// Same bucket across all pods — 100 req/min total, not 100 per pod!
```

